[1] Cholera - Tanzania (Dar es Salaam)
Date: Mon 13 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: IRIN [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/IRIN/2f58da04d74c47687367c4598482dba8
.htm>

Tanzania: Cholera outbreak leaves 79 in hospital, new cases continue
---------------------------------------------------------------------
New cases of cholera continue to be reported in Tanzania's commercial
capital, Dar es Salaam, where until Fri 10 Mar 2006, 79 patients were
admitted to various health centers in the city, a spokesman said on
Mon 13 Mar 2006.
"We are getting new cases almost every day despite the ongoing mass
education campaigns on how to contain the disease," Gaston Makwembe,
an information officer for the Dar es Salaam City Council, said. He
blamed the shortage of water in the city for the disease's
persistence, which has seen periodic outbreaks there and in other
parts of the country because of public consumption of unsafe drinking
water from wells and other sources.
He said 582 cholera patients were reported at various health centers
in the city since 2 Dec 2005, 6 of whom died.
--
