[2] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Sat 11 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=423776>

15 new cholera cases detected
-----------------------------------
15 new cholera cases, of which 11 occurred in Sambizanga district,
have been registered in the Angolan capital (Luanda) in the past 48
hours without claiming lives, announced the Provincial Health
Director, Vita Vemba.
Vita Vemba explained that, in the last 24 hours, 4 cases have been
registered, 3 in Sambizanga and one in Ingombota district of Luanda
province.
From the 196 cases reported, 11 people have died since the start of
the cholera outbreak, declared on 13 Feb 2006.
--
