[3] Cholera - Malawi
Date: Sat 11 Mar 2006
From: Pablo Nart <pablo.nart@terra.es>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/200603/11/eng20060311_249677.html>

Malawi records worst cholera outbreak in 4 years
-------------------------------------------------
Malawi has in 2006 recorded the country's worst cholera outbreak
since 2002, as 46 people have died from the recorded 3852 cases, a
senior government official told Xinhua on 10 Mar 2006.
"Although we have cholera outbreaks every year during the rainy
season, this year [2006] has been the worst compared to the past 4
years," said Habib Somanje, director of Preventive Health Services.
He said Malawi's commercial capital, Blantyre has been the worst hit,
with 1035 reported cases and 12 deaths.
Somanje, however, said this year's [2006] cholera affected only 5
districts of the country's total 28 districts. He attributed this
year's increased number of cholera cases to Malawi's hunger crisis,
which [has] severely affected close to 5 million people.
--
Pablo Nart
<pablo.nart@terra.es>
