[4] Cholera - Zambia (Chongwe District)
Date: Thu 9 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Zambia News Agency [edited]
<http://www.zana.gov.zm/news/viewnews.cgi?category=11&id=1141974637>

Chongwe records 25 cholera cases
----------------------------------
Chongwe District has recorded 25 cases of cholera, District Health
Management Team (DHMT) Director Dr. Charles Msiska has disclosed.
In an interview, Dr. Msiska announced that Ngwerere was the most
affected due to its poor sanitation and that the DHMT has embarked on
a campaign to freely distribute chlorine to the people in
cholera-affected areas in the district. However, Dr. Msiska said no
deaths had been recorded due to the quick response from the health
workers who treat the patients on site as opposed to transporting
them to health centers for treatment.
--
