[7] Cholera - Zimbabwe (Midlands Province)
Date: Mon 6 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200603/06/eng20060306_248304.html>

Cholera claims 6 in Zimbabwe
---------------------------------
6 people have died, and 137 people have contracted cholera in the
Midlands province in Zimbabwe over the past 3 weeks, reported the
Herald daily on Mon 6 Mar 2006.
Zimbabwean health officials said the cases were a result of unsafe
drinking water, which the rural folks fetched from rivers and open
wells. The officials have toured rural communities distributing
tablets for disinfecting drinking water.
--
