[8] Cholera - India (Karnataka), suspected
Date: Sun 12 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Deccan Herald [edited]
<http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/mar122006/state1923402006311.asp>

8 cholera cases in city
-----------------------
8 people have tested positive for cholera in Bangalore. The results
of tests on the stool samples sent to the Government Public Health
Institute after an outbreak of gastroenteritis in the city were
conveyed to the respective hospitals on Sat 11 Mar 2006. However, BMP
Chief Health Officer Dr. Thandava Murthy denied there are cases of
cholera.
The 3 cases in the Epidemic Disease Hospital are 2 adults and one
child from Seshadripuram, Srirampuram and Malleswaram. The 5 cases in
the Kempegowda Institute of Medical Sciences include 4 children and
one adult from Chamarajpet, Parvathipuram (near VV Puram) and
surrounding areas.
Dr. Murthy maintains there are only 10 cases of gastroenteritis
reported from Siddarthanagar near Goodshed Road.
Unconfirmed reports said that a 19-year-old from Vinayaknagar, in the
same Chickpet area, died at home due to cholera and that the entire
family had left for North Karnataka immediately afterwards.
--
